<h2 id="calculations">Calculations</h2>
<hr class="custom-hr" />
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      This guide assumes you have
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Living_Area#Canteen_and_Merchant"
        >Merchant</a
      >,
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Living_Area#Canteen_and_Merchant"
        >Oil Canteen</a
      >,
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Living_Area#Lecture_Hall"
        >Lecture Hall</a
      >, and all
      <a
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        href="https://azurlane.koumakan.jp/wiki/Daily_Raid">Daily Raids</a
      >
      to their maximum level.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Quantities are only listed if the resource is in high-demand, guaranteed,
      and/or as I deem fit.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          Quantities assume a player has not spent money and/or gems on these
          resources.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Only <b>guaranteed</b> drops are considered. You can get a lot more of
          these resources than listed depending on your RNG in commissions, shop
          rotations, map drops, etc.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Weeks are assumed to be 7 Days, Months are assumed to be 30 Days, and
          Months are assumed to be 4 Weeks long. This means quantities listed
          will be slightly underestimated due to how the calendar works.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          <b>Monthly</b> and <b>Bimonthly</b> are calculated seperately from each
          other. Bimonthly quantities aren't used in Monthly calculations. Daily
          and Weekly quantities are based on Monthly.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<br />

